<section id="auswahl">
<bookmark xml-lang="en-US" branch="index" id="bm_id3155963"><bookmark_value>selection options in formulas</bookmark_value>
<bookmark_value>formulas; selections</bookmark_value>
</bookmark>
<bookmark xml-lang="en-US" branch="hid/SID_TOOLBOX" id="bm_id3145789" localize="false"/><paragraph role="heading" id="hd_id3155963" xml-lang="en-US" level="1" l10n="U" oldref="1"><variable id="func_win"><link href="text/smath/01/03090000.xhp" name="Selection">Selection</link>
</variable></paragraph>
<paragraph role="paragraph" id="par_id3149500" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="U" oldref="2"><ahelp hid="SID_TOOLBOX">This is a list of operators, functions, symbols and format options that can be inserted into the formula.</ahelp></paragraph>
</section>
<paragraph role="paragraph" id="par_id3148699" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="U" oldref="5">Some <link href="text/smath/01/03090900.xhp" name="examples">examples</link> show you the range of operations. You can find more examples in the <emph>Samples - Formulas</emph> folder.</paragraph>
<paragraph role="paragraph" id="par_id3151244" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="U" oldref="6">The selection window is divided into two parts. Clicking a symbol at the top of the window displays its subordinate symbols in the lower half of the window.</paragraph>
<paragraph role="paragraph" id="par_id3153250" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="U" oldref="7">You can access the same functions in submenus through the context menu of the <emph>Commands</emph> window.</paragraph>
